challengeName: CSFV Games in  Offline Network Bug Hunting Part 1
detailedRequirements:
Project Overview

This project, the CSFV Community Gaming website project will provide the web site infrastructure and integration of the games. This will be a web site that is available on the Internet, and also will be delivered in a form where the server and the games can be installed and used behind a firewall.

The goal of this challenge is to test the first version of the website and games behind a firewall in an offline network (no access to internet).

Contest Objective

The goal of this competition is to clearly identify the limitations of the offline deployment and ensure the website and games work as expected against all required OSes and Browsers. Although we tried to disable all calls to the internet, we still see in games attempt to make calls to interent to get resources intead of making calls to the EC2 VM to obtain the resource, and we are trying in this challenge to identify these calls as well. So you need to make sure you can load the game and play it OK, and also report issues about accessing interent.

In order to simulate the offline environment, we have deployed the website and games into Amazon EC2 VM and disabled all outbounding network access and only allowed the VM to receive connections to http, https, and ssh ports.

Your task is to setup a proxy in your environment to block all requests to the internet except requests made to the website and games. Please follow the instructions below for how to setup the proxy in your browser and environment.

Things to test in the current competetion are:

  • The website :
    • The home page can load OK
    • User can register (on successful register, the user should be redirected to home page - no verification email or activation needed)
    • User can login to the website
    • User can use the carousal, header navigation, footer (games column) navigation to navigate to the games pages.
    • User can logout of the website
  • Games :
    • The following games are in scope :
      • Circuitbot
      • Flowjam
      • Ghostmap
    • User can load the game successfully
    • SSO - user should be able to login to website and navigate to the game which will recognize the user as logged in.
    • User can play the game and complete as many levels as possible.
      • User can see the levels completed when return back to the game (you need to close and reopen the game to verify this)
    • User should be able to login to the game if the user navigated to the game as non logged in.

Browser and Operation System Requirements

Chrome, Safari, and Firefox on Mac, and IE 7+, Firefox, and Chrome on Windows 7+.

Contest Guidelines

The guidelines for this contest are given below:

  • As issues are identified they need to be logged in JIRA.
  • Issues must include clear descriptions, test cases and steps to reproduce and expected vs. actual results in order to be counted.
  • Each issue must be related to specific OS and specific Browser. i.e. you must indicate that Windows 7 on IE browser. Don't mix browsers such as Chrome and IE in single ticket.
  • First competitor to find an issue gets credit, duplicates will not be counted.
  • Reviewers will accept, reject or mark the issues as duplicate.
  • Please DO take a look at the reported bugs, duplicated bugs cost your work time and the reviewer's time.

Important Notice:

You must also be the first person to report the issue and submit it while submission phase is open.  JIRA will allow you to file issues before and after the submission phase, but these will NOT be counted.

Technologies

  • Unity Plugin
  • Flash Plugin
  • HTML/CSS/Javascript

Testing VM

The website and games are deployed to this VM http://ec2-50-17-27-211.compute-1.amazonaws.com/

Proxy Setup

It's up to you to setup any proxy software available online as long as it does the job, we picked this one http://portswigger.net/burp/downloadfree.html here are setps to set it up and run successfully

  • Download the free burp proxy tool.
  • It is java app so run the file once download is done, it should open a page similar to this
  • Go to Proxy > Options tab, use default proxy listeners IP/Port (you can update it if port 8080 is occupied), and add new entry to "Intercept Client Requests" as shown in the screenshot
  • Go to Proxy > Intercept tab and click "intercept off" button to become "intercept on" (enable intercept)
  • Open your browser and set proxy, i.e. in fireforx go to Preferences > Advanced > Connection > click "setting" button. Set proxy as in screenshot, and click "OK" and close the preferences.
  • Go to browser and start testing http://ec2-50-17-27-211.compute-1.amazonaws.com/ you should load the website ok, if you try to hit any thing other than urls with the VM IP it should show you that page won't complete loading and interceptor will show there is a call being intercepted and you should take action, same as in screenshot. If that happens when playing the game or accessing the website, it means the page is trying to access a link outside the VM installation, you need to report that with all details (include screenshots if possible)
  • Since you are offline while doing the testing it is better to use offline excel sheet or word document to write down all issues you are having, then once youa re done, turn off "intercept" and go to jira to report the issues.
  • Note that you need to try different possiblities for intercepted calls, try to "Forward" it in order to continue the action you were trying to do, possiblity that if you "dropped" the call the page won't load or game won't work as expected.

Contest Prize Eligibility

The submitter with the most accepted bugs will win the contest. Other submitters will be rewarded $5 per accepted reported issue.
finalSubmissionGuidelines:
Bug Report Process

Bug Report Format

For each report of a limitation or bug, we need the following information:

  • Steps to reproduce, including any needed information
  • Include all the intercepted calls
  • Screen shots (if applicable)
  • Expected results after the bug is fixed
  • Current results, before the bug is fixed
  • Browser version
  • OS version

 Important Notice:

  • If you do not properly document your bug reports, they will likely be rejected due to lack of information or documentation. Also, make sure your bug reports are reasonably general.
  • If you submit the same bug that is seen in multiple screens, for instance, you will likely only get credit for the original bug report. The others will all be closed as duplicates.

Ticket Logging

You will log your tickets here: https://apps.topcoder.com/bugs/browse/CSFV and when creating a bug you MUST select the "Offline InstallDVD" component. Bugs will not be counted if a selection is not made.

Scoring

The Scoring guidelines followed for the contest are given below:

  • For scoring, the submitter with the most accepted bugs will win.
  • For submitters who submit but don't take first, if they submit bugs that aren't covered in the first place submission, they will receive $5 for each unique bug reported up to a maximum of the 1st place prize. 

 Important Notice:

If two submitters submit the same bug report, the submitter who submitted the report first into JIRA will get credit for the bug. The second submitter will not. 

Tips

Some of the tips helpful for the contest are:

  • Submitting what is obviously the same issue multiple times with small variations will only annoy the reviewer that has to sort through all the issues and will only count as one issue anyway. If it's less obvious if it is the same issue or not, use your best judgment and the reviewers will do the same.
  • Put an eye on the issues being submitted by other members to minimize the time you may be spending on duplicate efforts. Knowing what has already been reported will allow you to better focus your time on finding yet undiscovered issues.
  • Double check your steps to reproduce and test cases to make sure they are clear. Make sure your steps include creation of any necessary data.

Submission Deliverables

You need report your issues in JIRA. Please submit a text file contains the bugs you reported to OR.

Final Submission

  • For each member, the final submission should be uploaded to the Online Review Tool.
  • You must not include any identifying information, such as your handle, in your submission. Your submission should be anonymous and you will be scored down in screening for not complying.
